                            <comment id="12849636" author="larsgeorge" created="Thu, 25 Mar 2010 09:41:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hey KayKay,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I was wondering what that actually helps? You can already specify a combination of columns or families with the existing parameter. If you leave out a &quot;:&quot; divider then it is internally treated as a column family and addFamily is called, if it &lt;b&gt;does&lt;/b&gt; have a colon divider then it parses out family and column and adds them together. Please advise.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Lars&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12849721" author="streamy" created="Thu, 25 Mar 2010 15:14:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Agreed that this doesn&apos;t add a new feature.  But I&apos;m +1 on the jira because we should move everything to the new-API style of doing things.  family:qualifier is actually deprecated in the API, though we may retain it for quite some time anyways, having the mr api talk something that looks closer to the new API is not a bad idea.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;That being said, can&apos;t we just pass a Scan and do whatever we want?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12849829" author="kaykay.unique" created="Thu, 25 Mar 2010 18:39:46 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you leave out a &quot;:&quot; divider then it is internally treated as a column family and addFamily is called, if it does have a colon divider then it parses out family and column and adds them together. Please advise&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Good catch, Lars. This was not obvious when I was looking at the TIF to set the Configuration property for the family.  &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;That being said, can&apos;t we just pass a Scan and do whatever we want?&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;jgray, true. Programmatically - yes, using - TableMapReduceUtil.convertScanToString() , and setting it to conf should do the job.  I was initially maintaining the list of columns in hbase-site.xml and given the data locality of reference is w.r.t families anyway, it might be an useful addition to the TIF api, for easy configuration at .xml files with the alternative for Scan , available as appropriate, for cases beyond the same. &lt;/p&gt;

</comment>
                            <comment id="12849841" author="kaykay.unique" created="Thu, 25 Mar 2010 18:59:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Incorporating feedback.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Added a log warning for addColumn(byte[] family) to redirect  to addFamily(byte[] family) . &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Added a javadoc to TIF ,  config SCAN to how to retrieve the serialized Scan as it is not immediately obvious what the expected serialization format is.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12850735" author="kaykay.unique" created="Sun, 28 Mar 2010 21:29:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;looks ok - feedback check please . &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12851269" author="stack" created="Tue, 30 Mar 2010 06:05:39 +0000"  >&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
+      LOG.warn(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;Method Scan#addColumn(&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;byte&lt;/span&gt;[] family) is deprecated. Please use Scan#addFamily(&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;byte&lt;/span&gt;[] family) &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;for&lt;/span&gt; the same.&quot;&lt;/span&gt;);
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;.. is out of the ordinary in that we don&apos;t log anywhere when folks use deprecated APIs.  Convention is just marking API with &apos;@deprecated&apos; in javadoc.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Otherwise, patch looks good.  I can apply w/o the above warning if thats ok w/ you KK?&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="12851270" author="kaykay.unique" created="Tue, 30 Mar 2010 06:08:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;That&apos;s fine, stack. please go ahead. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12851272" author="stack" created="Tue, 30 Mar 2010 06:19:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed to trunk.  Thanks for the patch Kay Kay.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12851294" author="kaykay.unique" created="Tue, 30 Mar 2010 07:16:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks stack. Would it be ok to have this on the branch as well ? &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12851298" author="stack" created="Tue, 30 Mar 2010 07:32:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;.bq  Would it be ok to have this on the branch as well ? &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Done. Thanks for the patch Kay Kay.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
